HEADWORD: Exchangeability
<hw>Ex*change`a*bil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
quality or state of being exchangeable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The law ought not be contravened by an express article admitting
the <qex>exchangeability</qex> of such persons.</q>
<rj><qau>Washington.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

